Here is a Python solution using regex:
```python
import re

def extract_code(filename):
    pattern = r'\b\d{1,2}-[a-zA-Z0-9]{3}\.usfm\b'
    match = re.search(pattern, filename)

    if match:
        return match.group()
    else:
        return None
```
This function accepts a `filename` as an input and returns the extracted code if it exists in the given `filename`. If there is no match found then it will return `None`. 

Please note that this solution assumes that the three character code always follows the format "XX-XXX" where 'X' denotes any alphanumeric character (upper or lower case) and '0' to '9'.
